# Accessibility Conventions

## Semantic HTML first

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<div onClick={handleClick}>Submit</div>

// ✅ GOOD
<button type="button" onClick={handleClick}>Submit</button>
```

Use `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<header>`, `<section>` for page structure.

## Touch & keyboard (H5 + Pad)

- Min target 44×44px (`min-h-11 min-w-11`) — see `responsive-layout.mdc`
- Visible focus: rely on shadcn `focus-visible:` rings; don't remove outlines
- Interactive elements must be reachable via Tab

## ARIA

- Icon-only buttons: `aria-label="Close"`
- Form fields: associate `<label>` or `aria-labelledby`
- Live regions for toasts/async feedback: `aria-live="polite"`
- Don't add redundant `aria-*` on semantic elements

## Modals & dialogs (shadcn Dialog)

- Use `@ryx/ui` Dialog/Sheet when available
- Trap focus inside open modal; restore focus on close
- Close on Escape; backdrop click if product allows

## Images

- Meaningful images: descriptive `alt`
- Decorative images: `alt=""`
